cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with visual place recognition, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and proposal regions also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces a new descriptor for landmark features, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
